\title{Fda Database}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Query openFDA API for drugs, devices, adverse events, recalls, regulatory submissions (510k, PMA), substance identification (UNII), for FDA regulatory data analysis and safety research."}

\subtree{
\title{FDA Database Access}
\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{Access comprehensive FDA regulatory data through openFDA, the FDA's initiative to provide open APIs for public datasets. Query information about drugs, medical devices, foods, animal/veterinary products, and substances using Python with standardized interfaces.}

\p{\strong{Key capabilities:}}

\ul{
\li{Query adverse events for drugs, devices, foods, and veterinary products}
\li{Access product labeling, approvals, and regulatory submissions}
\li{Monitor recalls and enforcement actions}
\li{Look up National Drug Codes (NDC) and substance identifiers (UNII)}
\li{Analyze device classifications and clearances (510k, PMA)}
\li{Track drug shortages and supply issues}
\li{Research chemical structures and substance relationships}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\p{This skill should be used when working with:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Drug research}: Safety profiles, adverse events, labeling, approvals, shortages}
\li{\strong{Medical device surveillance}: Adverse events, recalls, 510(k) clearances, PMA approvals}
\li{\strong{Food safety}: Recalls, allergen tracking, adverse events, dietary supplements}
\li{\strong{Veterinary medicine}: Animal drug adverse events by species and breed}
\li{\strong{Chemical/substance data}: UNII lookup, CAS number mapping, molecular structures}
\li{\strong{Regulatory analysis}: Approval pathways, enforcement actions, compliance tracking}
\li{\strong{Pharmacovigilance}: Post-market surveillance, safety signal detection}
\li{\strong{Scientific research}: Drug interactions, comparative safety, epidemiological studies}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Start}
\subtree{
\title{1. Basic Setup}
\pre{\startverb
from scripts.fda_query import FDAQuery

# Initialize (API key optional but recommended)
fda = FDAQuery(api_key="YOUR_API_KEY")

# Query drug adverse events
events = fda.query_drug_events("aspirin", limit=100)

# Get drug labeling
label = fda.query_drug_label("Lipitor", brand=True)

# Search device recalls
recalls = fda.query("device", "enforcement",
                   search="classification:Class+I",
                   limit=50)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. API Key Setup}
\p{While the API works without a key, registering provides higher rate limits:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Without key}: 240 requests/min, 1,000/day}
\li{\strong{With key}: 240 requests/min, 120,000/day}
}

\p{Register at: https://open.fda.gov/apis/authentication/}

\p{Set as environment variable:}

\pre{\startverb
export FDA_API_KEY="your_key_here"
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Running Examples}
\pre{\startverb
# Run comprehensive examples
python scripts/fda_examples.py

# This demonstrates:
# - Drug safety profiles
# - Device surveillance
# - Food recall monitoring
# - Substance lookup
# - Comparative drug analysis
# - Veterinary drug analysis
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{FDA Database Categories}
\subtree{
\title{Drugs}
\p{Access 6 drug-related endpoints covering the full drug lifecycle from approval to post-market surveillance.}

\p{\strong{Endpoints:}}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Adverse Events} - Reports of side effects, errors, and therapeutic failures}
\li{\strong{Product Labeling} - Prescribing information, warnings, indications}
\li{\strong{NDC Directory} - National Drug Code product information}
\li{\strong{Enforcement Reports} - Drug recalls and safety actions}
\li{\strong{Drugs@FDA} - Historical approval data since 1939}
\li{\strong{Drug Shortages} - Current and resolved supply issues}
}

\p{\strong{Common use cases:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Safety signal detection
fda.count_by_field("drug", "event",
                  search="patient.drug.medicinalproduct:metformin",
                  field="patient.reaction.reactionmeddrapt")

# Get prescribing information
label = fda.query_drug_label("Keytruda", brand=True)

# Check for recalls
recalls = fda.query_drug_recalls(drug_name="metformin")

# Monitor shortages
shortages = fda.query("drug", "drugshortages",
                     search="status:Currently+in+Shortage")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Reference:} See \code{\startverb references/drugs.md\stopverb} for detailed documentation}
}

\subtree{
\title{Devices}
\p{Access 9 device-related endpoints covering medical device safety, approvals, and registrations.}

\p{\strong{Endpoints:}}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Adverse Events} - Device malfunctions, injuries, deaths}
\li{\strong{510(k) Clearances} - Premarket notifications}
\li{\strong{Classification} - Device categories and risk classes}
\li{\strong{Enforcement Reports} - Device recalls}
\li{\strong{Recalls} - Detailed recall information}
\li{\strong{PMA} - Premarket approval data for Class III devices}
\li{\strong{Registrations & Listings} - Manufacturing facility data}
\li{\strong{UDI} - Unique Device Identification database}
\li{\strong{COVID-19 Serology} - Antibody test performance data}
}

\p{\strong{Common use cases:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Monitor device safety
events = fda.query_device_events("pacemaker", limit=100)

# Look up device classification
classification = fda.query_device_classification("DQY")

# Find 510(k) clearances
clearances = fda.query_device_510k(applicant="Medtronic")

# Search by UDI
device_info = fda.query("device", "udi",
                       search="identifiers.id:00884838003019")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Reference:} See \code{\startverb references/devices.md\stopverb} for detailed documentation}
}

\subtree{
\title{Foods}
\p{Access 2 food-related endpoints for safety monitoring and recalls.}

\p{\strong{Endpoints:}}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Adverse Events} - Food, dietary supplement, and cosmetic events}
\li{\strong{Enforcement Reports} - Food product recalls}
}

\p{\strong{Common use cases:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Monitor allergen recalls
recalls = fda.query_food_recalls(reason="undeclared peanut")

# Track dietary supplement events
events = fda.query_food_events(
    industry="Dietary Supplements")

# Find contamination recalls
listeria = fda.query_food_recalls(
    reason="listeria",
    classification="I")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Reference:} See \code{\startverb references/foods.md\stopverb} for detailed documentation}
}

\subtree{
\title{Animal & Veterinary}
\p{Access veterinary drug adverse event data with species-specific information.}

\p{\strong{Endpoint:}}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Adverse Events} - Animal drug side effects by species, breed, and product}
}

\p{\strong{Common use cases:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Species-specific events
dog_events = fda.query_animal_events(
    species="Dog",
    drug_name="flea collar")

# Breed predisposition analysis
breed_query = fda.query("animalandveterinary", "event",
    search="reaction.veddra_term_name:*seizure*+AND+"
           "animal.breed.breed_component:*Labrador*")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Reference:} See \code{\startverb references/animal_veterinary.md\stopverb} for detailed documentation}
}

\subtree{
\title{Substances & Other}
\p{Access molecular-level substance data with UNII codes, chemical structures, and relationships.}

\p{\strong{Endpoints:}}

\ol{
\li{\strong{Substance Data} - UNII, CAS, chemical structures, relationships}
\li{\strong{NSDE} - Historical substance data (legacy)}
}

\p{\strong{Common use cases:}}

\pre{\startverb
# UNII to CAS mapping
substance = fda.query_substance_by_unii("R16CO5Y76E")

# Search by name
results = fda.query_substance_by_name("acetaminophen")

# Get chemical structure
structure = fda.query("other", "substance",
    search="names.name:ibuprofen+AND+substanceClass:chemical")
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Reference:} See \code{\startverb references/other.md\stopverb} for detailed documentation}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Query Patterns}
\subtree{
\title{Pattern 1: Safety Profile Analysis}
\p{Create comprehensive safety profiles combining multiple data sources:}

\pre{\startverb
def drug_safety_profile(fda, drug_name):
    """Generate complete safety profile."""

    # 1. Total adverse events
    events = fda.query_drug_events(drug_name, limit=1)
    total = events["meta"]["results"]["total"]

    # 2. Most common reactions
    reactions = fda.count_by_field(
        "drug", "event",
        search=f"patient.drug.medicinalproduct:*{drug_name}*",
        field="patient.reaction.reactionmeddrapt",
        exact=True
    )

    # 3. Serious events
    serious = fda.query("drug", "event",
        search=f"patient.drug.medicinalproduct:*{drug_name}*+AND+serious:1",
        limit=1)

    # 4. Recent recalls
    recalls = fda.query_drug_recalls(drug_name=drug_name)

    return {
        "total_events": total,
        "top_reactions": reactions["results"][:10],
        "serious_events": serious["meta"]["results"]["total"],
        "recalls": recalls["results"]
    }
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pattern 2: Temporal Trend Analysis}
\p{Analyze trends over time using date ranges:}

\pre{\startverb
from datetime import datetime, timedelta

def get_monthly_trends(fda, drug_name, months=12):
    """Get monthly adverse event trends."""
    trends = []

    for i in range(months):
        end = datetime.now() - timedelta(days=30*i)
        start = end - timedelta(days=30)

        date_range = f"[{start.strftime('%Y%m%d')}+TO+{end.strftime('%Y%m%d')}]"
        search = f"patient.drug.medicinalproduct:*{drug_name}*+AND+receivedate:{date_range}"

        result = fda.query("drug", "event", search=search, limit=1)
        count = result["meta"]["results"]["total"] if "meta" in result else 0

        trends.append({
            "month": start.strftime("%Y-%m"),
            "events": count
        })

    return trends
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pattern 3: Comparative Analysis}
\p{Compare multiple products side-by-side:}

\pre{\startverb
def compare_drugs(fda, drug_list):
    """Compare safety profiles of multiple drugs."""
    comparison = {}

    for drug in drug_list:
        # Total events
        events = fda.query_drug_events(drug, limit=1)
        total = events["meta"]["results"]["total"] if "meta" in events else 0

        # Serious events
        serious = fda.query("drug", "event",
            search=f"patient.drug.medicinalproduct:*{drug}*+AND+serious:1",
            limit=1)
        serious_count = serious["meta"]["results"]["total"] if "meta" in serious else 0

        comparison[drug] = {
            "total_events": total,
            "serious_events": serious_count,
            "serious_rate": (serious_count/total*100) if total > 0 else 0
        }

    return comparison
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pattern 4: Cross-Database Lookup}
\p{Link data across multiple endpoints:}

\pre{\startverb
def comprehensive_device_lookup(fda, device_name):
    """Look up device across all relevant databases."""

    return {
        "adverse_events": fda.query_device_events(device_name, limit=10),
        "510k_clearances": fda.query_device_510k(device_name=device_name),
        "recalls": fda.query("device", "enforcement",
                           search=f"product_description:*{device_name}*"),
        "udi_info": fda.query("device", "udi",
                            search=f"brand_name:*{device_name}*")
    }
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Working with Results}
\subtree{
\title{Response Structure}
\p{All API responses follow this structure:}

\pre{\startverb
{
    "meta": {
        "disclaimer": "...",
        "results": {
            "skip": 0,
            "limit": 100,
            "total": 15234
        }
    },
    "results": [
        # Array of result objects
    ]
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Error Handling}
\p{Always handle potential errors:}

\pre{\startverb
result = fda.query_drug_events("aspirin", limit=10)

if "error" in result:
    print(f"Error: {result['error']}")
elif "results" not in result or len(result["results"]) == 0:
    print("No results found")
else:
    # Process results
    for event in result["results"]:
        # Handle event data
        pass
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pagination}
\p{For large result sets, use pagination:}

\pre{\startverb
# Automatic pagination
all_results = fda.query_all(
    "drug", "event",
    search="patient.drug.medicinalproduct:aspirin",
    max_results=5000
)

# Manual pagination
for skip in range(0, 1000, 100):
    batch = fda.query("drug", "event",
                     search="...",
                     limit=100,
                     skip=skip)
    # Process batch
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Best Practices}
\subtree{
\title{1. Use Specific Searches}
\p{\strong{DO:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Specific field search
search="patient.drug.medicinalproduct:aspirin"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{DON'T:}}

\pre{\startverb
# Overly broad wildcard
search="*aspirin*"
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Implement Rate Limiting}
\p{The \code{\startverb FDAQuery\stopverb} class handles rate limiting automatically, but be aware of limits:}

\ul{
\li{240 requests per minute}
\li{120,000 requests per day (with API key)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Cache Frequently Accessed Data}
\p{The \code{\startverb FDAQuery\stopverb} class includes built-in caching (enabled by default):}

\pre{\startverb
# Caching is automatic
fda = FDAQuery(api_key=api_key, use_cache=True, cache_ttl=3600)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Use Exact Matching for Counting}
\p{When counting/aggregating, use \code{\startverb .exact\stopverb} suffix:}

\pre{\startverb
# Count exact phrases
fda.count_by_field("drug", "event",
                  search="...",
                  field="patient.reaction.reactionmeddrapt",
                  exact=True)  # Adds .exact automatically
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Validate Input Data}
\p{Clean and validate search terms:}

\pre{\startverb
def clean_drug_name(name):
    """Clean drug name for query."""
    return name.strip().replace('"', '\\"')

drug_name = clean_drug_name(user_input)
\stopverb}
}
}

